<i> This was one of my favorite
 books as a child.</i>

00:04:54.260 --> 00:04:57.663
"Under the Red Sea"
<i> by Dr. Prof. Hans Hass.</i>

00:04:57.663 --> 00:05:00.799
<i> He was an Austrian diving
 pioneer and biologist.</i>

00:05:00.799 --> 00:05:02.801
And you know, one of my biggest
wishes as a kid was to

00:05:02.801 --> 00:05:04.203
sort of, you know, be in one of

00:05:04.203 --> 00:05:06.406
you know, in the situations
that he found himself.

00:05:06.406 --> 00:05:08.507
And, you know, putting
this presentation together

00:05:08.507 --> 00:05:11.677
<i> I came across this image,
 and I went, "Sheesh.</i>

00:05:11.677 --> 00:05:13.612
<i> I've already had
 those experiences."</i>

00:05:13.612 --> 00:05:16.915
<i> So, you know, full circle, you
 know 12 years later and...</i>

00:05:16.915 --> 00:05:18.684
<i> thank you all so
 much for coming.</i>

